{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-04-17T15:30:34Z","content":"As a bilingual parent I would not want anything less for my child. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Merarys Rios","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90012867"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T01:08:37Z","content":"Offering a variety of educational choices will only benefit our community and our children.  FCPS is behind the curve on providing choices for students.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Dana Chaka","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89950082"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T01:16:56Z","content":"Spanish is part of my roots.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alberto Calimano","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7730985"},{"created_at":"2014-04-18T14:21:43Z","content":"We come from a spanish speaking culture and we would like for our daughter to learn spanish as good as english.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Juan Jimenez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90102860"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T21:27:48Z","content":"Spanish, like English and Mandarin, is one of the \"languages of the future\". It is also a language of the present. Children, adults, and society as a whole can only benefit from learning Spanish languages and the related cultures.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Justin Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90034376"},{"created_at":"2014-04-17T01:53:04Z","content":"Around 8% of your population is of Hispanic or Latino Origin. Most of the parents of children of Hispanic or Latino Origin are eager for their children to learn how to read AND write in Spanish, and about the differences in culture and history. Of the rest of Frederick County's population who is not of this origin, most see learning the second most spoken language in the world as an advantage for their children. Learning a Spanish as a second language increases their probability of getting the best jobs in the future. Please, do NOT fall behind. All other counties in the Washington Metropolitan Area offer this opportunity. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ana Montalvo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20165689"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T19:34:18Z","content":"The Hispanic population continues to increase in the U.S.  and the interest of learning Spanish too.  Learning Spanish at and early age is important because it may be seen as  a more natural process for the child. In this global economy, hand-in-hand with education, the more languages a person knows, the better the opportunities that he\\she may have to be a productive individual.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Norma Garcia","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92871236"}]}